comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T21:59:02.798Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check 2026-07-13: existing validate,deps visualization,and one-time living-map audits do not provide schema-aware graph coverage profiles and remediation plans; this extends canonical governance rather than replacing those items."
body: "## Finding families\n\n- Integrity: missing endpoints, unregistered kinds, invalid payloads, duplicate canonical identity, self-links, inverse mismatch.\n- Ordering: genuine cycles, stale blockers, contradictory blocks pairs, unreachable prerequisites, redundant transitive edges.\n- Coverage: unexplained roots or isolates, stories without delivery links, bodies naming absent prerequisites, milestones without outcomes, work without evidence lineage.\n- Temporal: stale inferred relationships, superseded endpoints, snapshot drift, history and materialized-view disagreement.\n- Quality: generic related overuse, alias drift, dense cliques, hub inflation, low-confidence edges without evidence.\n\n## Policy stance\n\nSparse is not automatically bad and dense is not automatically good. Every finding must state the violated policy, evidence, confidence, consequences, and safe next action. Waivers are explicit, attributable, scoped, reviewable, and time-aware."
